Kowloon's Black Ledger analysis focuses on the institutional design failure: why were two institutions allowed to maintain competing succession records for the same authority chain? The Neon Covenant's document architecture separates record-keeping from enforcement authority specifically to prevent Schism conditions. Kowloon position: the Schism was not caused by the water shortage — the water shortage was the trigger. The Schism was caused by a governance design that positioned two institutions as competitors over the same resource with the same authority. The Jade Clerks' inter-institutional document sharing requirements trace to the Schism: any legally authoritative record must be available for review by institutions with standing to challenge it.

