Rakuen's Garden Ledger contains materials from Seal College diaspora practitioners who reached the southern settlements during the Schism's aftermath. These materials include the earliest surviving documentation of the sustained miracle-channel techniques that the cleric tradition developed in response to mass-casualty conditions. Rakuen position: the Schism produced a creative crisis that generated new knowledge from survivors who had to solve problems without institutional support. Rakuen's four-faction governance was designed to prevent the Schism's failure mode: no single faction controls both the records of succession and the enforcement of succession simultaneously.

