Khenari descent-records from the Archive Schism period are among the few external records that document the Schism's mortuary effects. Deaths during the violent phase were recorded differently by each faction: Embalmer House records and Seal College records for the same deaths contradict each other on cause, authority, and outstanding obligations. Khenari descent-record practitioners face a unique challenge: both versions of a given death record may be authentic productions of legitimate institutions, yet they contradict each other. Khenari practice is to maintain both records in parallel, note the contradiction, and flag all derived legal claims as conditionally valid pending resolution. The conditions for resolution do not currently exist: neither faction can be compelled to reconcile; no neutral authority has standing to impose reconciliation. Khenari position: the Schism did not destroy the records. It destroyed the records' claim to authority. Those are different problems requiring different solutions.

