The Umbral's shadow-archives beneath Midgaard contain non-Solar-Court records of the Archive Schism period: observations made by Umbral archivists not embedded in either faction's record-keeping structure. These records are the closest thing to neutral documentation of the Schism available. Umbral shadow-archive records from the period document primarily what was absent: which administrative functions stopped operating, which locations were evacuated, which record types disappeared from circulation. The Umbral's observational mode — noting absence before presence — produced a record that neither faction's documentation captures. Umbral in Midgaard have made these records available to the Violet Compact for provenance review; the Compact uses them as calibration material for assessing Schism-era document authenticity. Umbral position: both factions kept records of what they did. Neither kept records of what they stopped doing. The shadow-archives kept records of the stopping.
